			<p>I Stumbled upon The Last Question a while back and found it intriguing, however I think I enjoyed this more for some reason. Perhaps because Murray&#8217;s way of thinking reminds me of my own, I&#8217;m not certain. </p>
<p>I&#8217;ve thought on the topic of everlasting existence a lot. I personally believe in God, and in an everlasting existence in whatever form, you&#8217;d never stop learning about God because He is infinite. You&#8217;d have to learn about everything he knew before you existed, and then catch up on what his thoughts have been since you existed and onward.</p>
			
			
