			<p>The Name &#8220;I Am&#8221; is beautiful in its simplicity and extremely awe provoking in its power. We often use the term &#8220;I am&#8221;  when describing ourselves but we always attach it to some finite attribute or character trait i.e., I am..a plumber, teacher&#8230;or I am angry, surprised. We as humans can never describe ourselves in terms of a single phrase; &#8220;I am&#8221;. However, the Eternal One, whom I identify as God says so without qualification. God&#8217;s eternal nature is the answer to any question of what, when, where, why, and who that lies beyond our comprehension. I applaud and admire Asimov&#8217;s genius.</p>
			
			
